The same Abbé celebrated mass more than once over the body of a woman
and with the blood of a child, sacrificed for the occasion, in the
chalice (see section on Sacrifice). The woman, who served as the altar
for these masses, was always nude, and was the person for whose benefit
the ceremony was performed. Marguerite Montvoisin makes this clear:

