The chief authorities all agree as to the fact of animal sacrifices.
Cotta compares it with the sacrifices offered by the heathen:

' Some bring their cursed Sorcery vnto their wished end by sacrificing
vnto the Diuell some liuing creatures, as *Serres* likewise witnesseth,
from the confession of Witches in *Henry* the fourth of *France*
deprehended, among whom, one confessed to haue offered vnto his Deuill
