The 'conjuring of cats' was a distinct feature, and is clearly derived
from an early form of sacrifice. The details are recorded only in
Scotland, and it is possible that Scotland is the only country in which
it occurred, though the sanctity of the cat in other places suggests
that the omission in the records is accidental.

